\end{equation}
and the product formation rate of the secondary reaction has reached its limiting value .
Notice that by assuming that the secondary reaction is fast enough to virtually adhere to $\boldsymbol{x}^{\ast}$ implies $V_2 > k_2c_1^{\max}$ .
Thus , this assumption admits an automatic partition of parameter space , and we will only consider regions of parameter space within which $V_2 > k_2c_1^{\max}=k_2\varepsilon_1 s_1^0$ holds .

